Celebrating my angel today.  5 years ago on this day, my life changed forever.  Leo, you are my princess.  You’re so joyful, confident, generous, kind & passionate.  I love your strength & your sweetness. I love the way you always want us to give money to the homeless man. I love when you want to cook diner with me.  I love when we lay in bed when you can’t sleep & just talk about nothing.  I love the way you hold my face when you kiss me.  I love when you sing on the way to school.  I love that you pick out your own clothes to wear everyday. I love the way you keep your brother in check.  I love the way that you care for others. I love all the little drawings you do for me.  I love the way that you know when Dad needs a hug.  I love our bike rides.  I love when we dance to John Legend.  I love when you say “hold me Dadda”. I love that you know how beautiful you are & I love that you know ‘who’s’ you are.  But most of all, I simply just love that fact that God gave me you.  One day I will give you away to an amazing man of God who will cherish, lead and protect you, but until then I’m going to make the most of every single day that you’re mine. HBD baby girl xx

Today was my baby girls 1st day of kindergarten!  I desperately tried to get the perfect little Insta pic of her, to celebrate her special day…but that didn’t happen lol!  She didn’t want to wear her hair down, wouldn’t  keep still for a single pic & for some reason insisted in standing on one leg for most of the pics 😬🤦🏻‍♂️. Initially I was frustrated, until I remembered, that this is who my baby girl is!  She’s wild, creative, precious,  strong, fun & so much more.  So these pics aren’t exactly ‘Insta perfect’, but they depict  exactly who this little angel is…& I’m so grateful to God for that ❤️

After my little social media hiatus I thought I’d give you all a brief life update.  My departure from FC has definitely been one of the harder transitions that I’ve had to make,  but I’ve already learnt so much through this journey & for that, I’m grateful.  After 19 years of full time ministry,  pastoring & preaching,  I certainly never expected to find myself pursuing anything other than ministry. However,  sometimes it’s through unexpected challenges that God unlocks unexpected opportunities, and this is what I’m praying and believing for in this next season.  Luca & Leo continue to keep life busy & fun all at once.  It’s been a month of football games,  princess dress ups,  fall festivals & more missing teeth.  The three of us miss our Free Chapel OC family beyond words,  but we’re so grateful that His church isn’t confined to a service or a building, but continues to thrive through community & life long relationships.  We are so excited for whatever God has next for us 
🙏🏻😊

I’m so thankful that God’s hand has been on us this year.  I’m thankful for the power of prayer.  I’m thankful that He has directed every step. I’m thankful for His peace that has surpassed our understanding.  I’m thankful for the amazing friendships that we have around us.  I’m thankful for the difficult things that we’ve encountered that have made us stronger & grown our faith.  I’m thankful that our best days are ahead of us.

Happy Thanksgiving 🙏🏻❤️
